<paragraph id="50584915FF97525DFF4D1A430EBDFA1C" blockId="17.[151,1436,1294,1514]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
It has long been apparent that this species was misplaced in 
<emphasis id="62939507FF97525DFCB51A4208C3FADE" box="[879,997,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="97E73296FF97525DFCB51A4208C7FADE" box="[879,993,1295,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scortizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scortizus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Characters that place this species in 
<taxonomicName id="97E73296FF97525DFF4D1A780A1AFAB8" box="[151,316,1333,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Onorelucanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="62939507FF97525DFF4D1A780A1AFAB8" box="[151,316,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Onorelucanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include the simple male genitalic capsule; convex, unarmed pronotum; and toothed mesotibiae and metatibiae in both sexes. The name 
<taxonomicName id="97E73296FF97525DFDA31A110842FA80" authority="Fukinuki" authorityName="Fukinuki" box="[633,868,1372,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scortizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ismaeli">
<emphasis id="62939507FF97525DFDA31A1109CBFA83" box="[633,749,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">S. ismaeli</emphasis>
Fukinuki
</taxonomicName>
, represents a mandibular variant from the same locality as 
<emphasis id="62939507FF97525DFEC21ACE0AE5FA6A" box="[280,451,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="97E73296FF97525DFEC21ACE0A98FA6A" box="[280,446,1411,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scortizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverosus">O. pulverosus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
We have examined intermediate forms, and thus the name is reduced to synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="97E73296FF97525DFF0F1AE40A5BFA34" box="[213,381,1449,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scortizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverosus">
<emphasis id="62939507FF97525DFF0F1AE40A5BFA34" box="[213,381,1449,1474]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">O. pulverosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This situation exemplifies the undesirability of naming new species based on a single specimen and without a detailed study of the genus as a whole, or at the very least, some form of peer review.
</paragraph>
